{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I thought in getting up to my TED wish"},{"time":6000,"text":"I would try to begin by putting in \nperspective what I try to do"},{"time":13000,"text":"and how it fits with what they try to do."},{"time":17000,"text":"We live in a world that everyone knows is interdependent,"},{"time":22000,"text":"but insufficient in three major ways."},{"time":28000,"text":"It is, first of all, profoundly unequal:"},{"time":31000,"text":"half the world's people still living on less than two dollars a day;"},{"time":35000,"text":"a billion people with no access to clean water;"},{"time":37000,"text":"two and a half billion no access to sanitation;"},{"time":40000,"text":"a billion going to bed hungry every night;"},{"time":42000,"text":"one in four deaths every year from AIDS, TB, malaria"},{"time":47000,"text":"and the variety of infections associated with dirty water --"},{"time":51000,"text":"80 percent of them under five years of age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54000,"text":"Even in wealthy countries it is common now to see inequality growing."},{"time":60000,"text":"In the United States, since 2001 we've had five years of economic growth,"},{"time":65000,"text":"five years of productivity growth in the workplace,"},{"time":68000,"text":"but median wages are stagnant and the percentage of working families"},{"time":72000,"text":"dropping below the poverty line is up by four percent."},{"time":76000,"text":"The percentage of working families without health care up by four percent."},{"time":80000,"text":"So this interdependent world which has been pretty good to most of us --"},{"time":84000,"text":"which is why we're all here in Northern California doing what we do"},{"time":88000,"text":"for a living, enjoying this evening -- is profoundly unequal."},{"time":93000,"text":"It is also unstable."},{"time":96000,"text":"Unstable because of the threats of terror,"},{"time":100000,"text":"weapons of mass destruction, the spread of global disease"},{"time":103000,"text":"and a sense that we are vulnerable to it in a way that we weren't not so many years ago."},{"time":110000,"text":"And perhaps most important of all, it is unsustainable"},{"time":114000,"text":"because of climate change, resource depletion and species destruction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"When I think about the world I would like to leave to my daughter"},{"time":126000,"text":"and the grandchildren I hope to have,"},{"time":128000,"text":"it is a world that moves away from unequal, unstable, unsustainable"},{"time":135000,"text":"interdependence to integrated communities -- locally, nationally and globally --"},{"time":140000,"text":"that share the characteristics of all successful communities:"},{"time":143000,"text":"a broadly shared, accessible set of opportunities,"},{"time":149000,"text":"a shared sense of responsibility for the success of the common enterprise"},{"time":153000,"text":"and a genuine sense of belonging."},{"time":159000,"text":"All easier said than done."},{"time":162000,"text":"When the terrorist incidents occurred in the United Kingdom a couple of years ago,"},{"time":168000,"text":"I think even though they didn't claim as many lives as we lost in the United States on 9/11,"},{"time":173000,"text":"I think the thing that troubled the British most"},{"time":175000,"text":"was that the perpetrators were not invaders, but homegrown citizens"},{"time":180000,"text":"whose religious and political identities were more important to them"},{"time":185000,"text":"than the people they grew up with, went to school with,"},{"time":188000,"text":"worked with, shared weekends with, shared meals with."},{"time":191000,"text":"In other words, they thought their differences"},{"time":194000,"text":"were more important than their common humanity."},{"time":198000,"text":"It is the central psychological plague of humankind in the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"Into this mix, people like us, who are not in public office,"},{"time":210000,"text":"have more power to do good than at any time in history,"},{"time":215000,"text":"because more than half the world's people"},{"time":217000,"text":"live under governments they voted in and can vote out."},{"time":220000,"text":"And even non-democratic governments are more sensitive to public opinion."},{"time":224000,"text":"Because primarily of the power of the Internet,"},{"time":229000,"text":"people of modest means can band together and amass vast sums of money"},{"time":235000,"text":"that can change the world for some public good if they all agree."},{"time":239000,"text":"When the tsunami hit South Asia, the United States contributed 1.2 billion dollars."},{"time":244000,"text":"30 percent of our households gave."},{"time":246000,"text":"Half of them gave over the Internet."},{"time":248000,"text":"The median contribution was somewhere around 57 dollars."},{"time":254000,"text":"And thirdly, because of the rise of non-governmental organizations."},{"time":259000,"text":"They, businesses, other citizens' groups, have enormous power"},{"time":265000,"text":"to affect the lives of our fellow human beings."},{"time":270000,"text":"When I became president in 1993,"},{"time":272000,"text":"there were none of these organizations in Russia."},{"time":274000,"text":"There are now a couple of hundred thousand."},{"time":276000,"text":"None in India. There are now at least a half a million active."},{"time":280000,"text":"None in China. There are now 250,000 registered with the government,"},{"time":283000,"text":"probably twice again that many who are not registered for political reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"When I organized my foundation, and I thought about the world as it is"},{"time":297000,"text":"and the world that I hope to leave to the next generation,"},{"time":302000,"text":"and I tried to be realistic about what I had cared about all my life"},{"time":309000,"text":"that I could still have an impact on."},{"time":311000,"text":"I wanted to focus on activities"},{"time":314000,"text":"that would help to alleviate poverty, fight disease, combat climate change,"},{"time":321000,"text":"bridge the religious, racial and other divides that torment the world,"},{"time":325000,"text":"but to do it in a way that would either use"},{"time":329000,"text":"whatever particular skills we could put together in our group"},{"time":335000,"text":"to change the way some public good function was performed"},{"time":340000,"text":"so that it would sweep across the world more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"You saw one reference to that in what we were able to do with AIDS drugs."},{"time":349000,"text":"And I want to say that the head of our AIDS effort,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and the person who also is primarily active in the wish I'll make tonight,"},{"time":356000,"text":"Ira Magaziner, is here with me and I want to thank him for everything he's done."},{"time":360000,"text":"He's over there."},{"time":362000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":366000,"text":"When I got out of office and was asked to work, first in the Caribbean,"},{"time":372000,"text":"to try to help deal with the AIDS crisis,"},{"time":375000,"text":"generic drugs were available for about 500 dollars a person a year."},{"time":379000,"text":"If you bought them in vast bulks,"},{"time":381000,"text":"you could get them at a little under 400 dollars."},{"time":384000,"text":"The first country we went to work in, the Bahamas,"},{"time":387000,"text":"was paying 3,500 dollars for these drugs."},{"time":389000,"text":"The market was so terribly disorganized"},{"time":392000,"text":"that they were buying this medicine through two agents"},{"time":396000,"text":"who were gigging them sevenfold."},{"time":399000,"text":"So the very first week we were working,"},{"time":402000,"text":"we got the price down to 500 dollars."},{"time":404000,"text":"And all of a sudden, they could save seven times as many lives"},{"time":406000,"text":"for the same amount of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"Then we went to work with the manufacturers of AIDS medicines,"},{"time":411000,"text":"one of whom was cited in the film,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and negotiated a whole different change in business strategy,"},{"time":418000,"text":"because even at 500 dollars, these drugs"},{"time":421000,"text":"were being sold on a high-margin, low-volume, uncertain-payment basis."},{"time":426000,"text":"So we worked on improving the productivity of the operations"},{"time":430000,"text":"and the supply chain, and went to a low-margin, high-volume,"},{"time":434000,"text":"absolutely certain-payment business."},{"time":436000,"text":"I joked that the main contribution we made"},{"time":439000,"text":"to the battle against AIDS was to get the manufacturers"},{"time":440000,"text":"to change from a jewelry store to a grocery store strategy."},{"time":446000,"text":"But the price went to 140 dollars from 500."},{"time":450000,"text":"And pretty soon, the average price was 192 dollars."},{"time":454000,"text":"Now we can get it for about 100 dollars."},{"time":456000,"text":"Children's medicine was 600 dollars,"},{"time":458000,"text":"because nobody could afford to buy any of it."},{"time":460000,"text":"We negotiated it down to 190."},{"time":463000,"text":"Then, the French imposed their brilliantly conceived airline tax"},{"time":467000,"text":"to create a something called UNITAID,"},{"time":469000,"text":"got a bunch of other countries to help."},{"time":471000,"text":"That children's medicine is now 60 dollars a person a year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"The only thing that is keeping us from basically saving the lives"},{"time":479000,"text":"of everybody who needs the medicine to stay alive"},{"time":481000,"text":"are the absence of systems necessary to diagnose, treat and care"},{"time":484000,"text":"for people and deliver this medicine."},{"time":488000,"text":"We started a childhood obesity initiative with the Heart Association in America."},{"time":492000,"text":"We tried to do the same thing by negotiating industry-right deals"},{"time":495000,"text":"with the soft drink and the snack food industry to cut the caloric"},{"time":500000,"text":"and other dangerous content of food going to our children in the schools."},{"time":504000,"text":"We just reorganized the markets."},{"time":507000,"text":"And it occurred to me that in this whole non-governmental world,"},{"time":512000,"text":"somebody needs to be thinking about organizing public goods markets."},{"time":517000,"text":"And that is now what we're trying to do,"},{"time":519000,"text":"and working with this large cities group to fight climate change,"},{"time":522000,"text":"to negotiate huge, big, volume deals that will enable cities"},{"time":527000,"text":"which generate 75 percent of the world's greenhouse gases,"},{"time":530000,"text":"to drastically and quickly reduce greenhouse gas emissions"},{"time":533000,"text":"in a way that is good economics."},{"time":537000,"text":"And this whole discussion as if it's some sort of economic burden,"},{"time":541000,"text":"is a mystery to me."},{"time":542000,"text":"I think it's a bird's nest on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"When Al Gore won his well-deserved Oscar"},{"time":548000,"text":"for the \"Inconvenient Truth\" movie, I was thrilled,"},{"time":552000,"text":"but I had urged him to make a second movie quickly."},{"time":556000,"text":"For those of you who saw \"An Inconvenient Truth,\""},{"time":560000,"text":"the most important slide in the Gore lecture is the last one,"},{"time":565000,"text":"which shows here's where greenhouse gases are going"},{"time":568000,"text":"if we don't do anything, here's where they could go."},{"time":570000,"text":"And then there are six different categories"},{"time":572000,"text":"of things we can do to change the trajectory."},{"time":574000,"text":"We need a movie on those six categories."},{"time":577000,"text":"And all of you need to have it embedded in your brains"},{"time":580000,"text":"and to organize yourselves around it."},{"time":583000,"text":"So we're trying to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"So organizing these markets is one thing we try to do."},{"time":588000,"text":"Now we have taken on a second thing, and this gets to my wish."},{"time":592000,"text":"It has been my experience in working in developing countries"},{"time":597000,"text":"that while the headlines may all be -- the pessimistic headlines may say,"},{"time":601000,"text":"well, we can't do this, that or the other thing because of corruption --"},{"time":605000,"text":"I think incapacity is a far bigger problem in poor countries than corruption,"},{"time":611000,"text":"and feeds corruption."},{"time":615000,"text":"We now have the money, given these low prices, to distribute"},{"time":618000,"text":"AIDS drugs all over the world to people we cannot presently reach."},{"time":625000,"text":"Today these low prices are available in the 25 countries where we work,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and in a total of 62 countries,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and about 550,000 people are getting the benefits of them."},{"time":635000,"text":"But the money is there to reach others."},{"time":638000,"text":"The systems are not there to reach the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641000,"text":"So what we have been trying to do,"},{"time":649000,"text":"working first in Rwanda and then in Malawi and other places --"},{"time":655000,"text":"but I want to talk about Rwanda tonight --"},{"time":657000,"text":"is to develop a model for rural health care in a very poor area"},{"time":665000,"text":"that can be used to deal with AIDS, TB, malaria, other infectious diseases,"},{"time":669000,"text":"maternal and child health, and a whole range of health issues"},{"time":672000,"text":"poor people are grappling with in the developing world,"},{"time":675000,"text":"that can first be scaled for the whole nation of Rwanda,"},{"time":679000,"text":"and then will be a model that could literally"},{"time":681000,"text":"be implemented in any other poor country in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683000,"text":"And the test is: one, will it do the job?"},{"time":685000,"text":"Will it provide high quality care?"},{"time":688000,"text":"And two, will it do it at a price"},{"time":690000,"text":"that will enable the country to sustain a health care system"},{"time":694000,"text":"without foreign donors after five to 10 years?"},{"time":698000,"text":"Because the longer I deal with these problems,"},{"time":702000,"text":"the more convinced I am that we have to --"},{"time":704000,"text":"whether it's economics, health, education, whatever --"},{"time":707000,"text":"we have to build systems."},{"time":709000,"text":"And the absence of systems that function"},{"time":712000,"text":"break the connection which got you all in this seat tonight."},{"time":716000,"text":"You think about whatever your life has been,"},{"time":718000,"text":"however many obstacles you have faced in your life,"},{"time":721000,"text":"at critical junctures you always knew"},{"time":724000,"text":"there was a predictable connection between the effort you exerted"},{"time":728000,"text":"and the result you achieved."},{"time":730000,"text":"In a world with no systems, with chaos,"},{"time":735000,"text":"everything becomes a guerilla struggle,"},{"time":738000,"text":"and this predictability is not there."},{"time":741000,"text":"And it becomes almost impossible to save lives,"},{"time":744000,"text":"educate kids, develop economies, whatever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"The person, in my view,"},{"time":750000,"text":"who has done the best job of this in the health care area,"},{"time":755000,"text":"of building a system in a very poor area, is Dr. Paul Farmer,"},{"time":759000,"text":"who, many of you know, has worked for now 20 years with his group,"},{"time":764000,"text":"Partners in Health, primarily in Haiti where he started,"},{"time":768000,"text":"but they've also worked in Russia, in Peru"},{"time":770000,"text":"and other places around the world."},{"time":772000,"text":"As poor as Haiti is, in the area where Farmer's clinic is active --"},{"time":777000,"text":"and they serve a catchment area far greater"},{"time":779000,"text":"than the medical professionals they have would indicate they could serve --"},{"time":783000,"text":"since 1988, they have not lost one person to tuberculosis, not one."},{"time":790000,"text":"And they've achieved a lot of other amazing health results."},{"time":795000,"text":"So when we decided to work in Rwanda"},{"time":799000,"text":"on trying to dramatically increase the income of the country and fight the AIDS problem,"},{"time":804000,"text":"we wanted to build a healthcare network,"},{"time":806000,"text":"because it had been totally destroyed during the genocide in 1994,"},{"time":810000,"text":"and the per capita income was still under a dollar a day."},{"time":814000,"text":"So I rang up, asked Paul Farmer if he would help."},{"time":819000,"text":"Because it seemed to me if we could prove there was a model in Haiti"},{"time":822000,"text":"and a model in Rwanda that we could then take all over the country,"},{"time":826000,"text":"number one, it would be a wonderful thing for a country"},{"time":828000,"text":"that has suffered as much as any on Earth in the last 15 years,"},{"time":832000,"text":"and number two, we would have something that could then be adapted"},{"time":836000,"text":"to any other poor country anywhere in the world."},{"time":840000,"text":"And so we have set about doing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844000,"text":"Now, we started working together 18 months ago."},{"time":848000,"text":"And we're working in an area called Southern Kayonza,"},{"time":852000,"text":"which is one of the poorest areas in Rwanda,"},{"time":856000,"text":"with a group that originally includes about 400,000 people."},{"time":862000,"text":"We're essentially implementing what Paul Farmer did in Haiti:"},{"time":867000,"text":"he develops and trains paid community health workers"},{"time":872000,"text":"who are able to identify health problems,"},{"time":876000,"text":"ensure that people who have AIDS or TB are properly diagnosed"},{"time":880000,"text":"and take their medicine regularly,"},{"time":882000,"text":"who work on bringing about health education, clean water and sanitation,"},{"time":889000,"text":"providing nutritional supplements and moving people up the chain of health care"},{"time":894000,"text":"if they have problems of the severity that require it."},{"time":898000,"text":"The procedures that make this work have been perfected,"},{"time":903000,"text":"as I said, by Paul Farmer and his team"},{"time":906000,"text":"in their work in rural Haiti over the last 20 years."},{"time":909000,"text":"Recently we did an evaluation of the first 18 months of our efforts in Rwanda."},{"time":915000,"text":"And the results were so good that the Rwandan government"},{"time":920000,"text":"has now agreed to adopt the model for the entire country,"},{"time":923000,"text":"and has strongly supported and put the full resources of the government behind it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"I'll tell you a little bit about our team because it's indicative of what we do."},{"time":933000,"text":"We have about 500 people around the world"},{"time":936000,"text":"working in our AIDS program, some of them for nothing --"},{"time":940000,"text":"just for transportation, room and board."},{"time":942000,"text":"And then we have others working in these other related programs."},{"time":946000,"text":"Our business plan in Rwanda"},{"time":948000,"text":"was put together under the leadership of Diana Noble,"},{"time":951000,"text":"who is an unusually gifted woman,"},{"time":954000,"text":"but not unusual in the type of people who have been willing to do this kind of work."},{"time":959000,"text":"She was the youngest partner at Schroder Ventures in London in her 20s."},{"time":964000,"text":"She was CEO of a successful e-venture --"},{"time":966000,"text":"she started and built Reed Elsevier Ventures --"},{"time":970000,"text":"and at 45 she decided she wanted to do something different with her life."},{"time":973000,"text":"So she now works full-time on this for very little pay."},{"time":977000,"text":"She and her team of former business people have created a business plan"},{"time":981000,"text":"that will enable us to scale this health system up for the whole country."},{"time":985000,"text":"And it would be worthy of the kind of private equity work"},{"time":990000,"text":"she used to do when she was making a lot more money for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"When we came to this rural area, 45 percent of the children under the age of five"},{"time":999000,"text":"had stunted growth due to malnutrition."},{"time":1004000,"text":"23 percent of them died before they reached the age of five."},{"time":1012000,"text":"Mortality at birth was over two-and-a-half percent."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Over 15 percent of the deaths among adults and children occurred"},{"time":1019000,"text":"because of intestinal parasites and diarrhea from dirty water and inadequate sanitation --"},{"time":1024000,"text":"all entirely preventable and treatable."},{"time":1027000,"text":"Over 13 percent of the deaths were from respiratory illnesses --"},{"time":1031000,"text":"again, all preventable and treatable."},{"time":1034000,"text":"And not a single soul in this area was being treated for AIDS or tuberculosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040000,"text":"Within the first 18 months, the following things happened:"},{"time":1044000,"text":"we went from zero to about 2,000 people being treated for AIDS."},{"time":1048000,"text":"That's 80 percent of the people who need treatment in this area."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Listen to this: less than four-tenths of one percent of those being treated"},{"time":1057000,"text":"stopped taking their medicine or otherwise defaulted on treatment."},{"time":1061000,"text":"That's lower than the figure in the United States."},{"time":1064000,"text":"Less than three-tenths of one percent"},{"time":1066000,"text":"had to transfer to the more expensive second-line drugs."},{"time":1071000,"text":"400,000 pregnant women were brought into counseling"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and will give birth for the first time within an organized healthcare system."},{"time":1080000,"text":"That's about 43 percent of all the pregnancies."},{"time":1085000,"text":"About 40 percent of all the people -- I said 400,000. I meant 40,000."},{"time":1089000,"text":"About 40 percent of all the people who need TB treatment are now getting it --"},{"time":1093000,"text":"in just 18 months, up from zero when we started."},{"time":1097000,"text":"43 percent of the children in need of an infant feeding program"},{"time":1100000,"text":"to prevent malnutrition and early death"},{"time":1102000,"text":"are now getting the food supplements they need to stay alive and to grow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"We've started the first malaria treatment programs they've ever had there."},{"time":1109000,"text":"Patients admitted to a hospital that was destroyed during the genocide"},{"time":1114000,"text":"that we have renovated along with four other clinics,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"complete with solar power generators, good lab technology."},{"time":1124000,"text":"We now are treating 325 people a month,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"despite the fact that almost 100 percent of the AIDS patients are now treated at home."},{"time":1135000,"text":"And the most important thing is"},{"time":1138000,"text":"because we've implemented Paul Farmer's model, using community health workers,"},{"time":1143000,"text":"we estimate that this system could be put into place for all of Rwanda"},{"time":1149000,"text":"for between five and six percent of GDP,"},{"time":1153000,"text":"and that the government could sustain that"},{"time":1157000,"text":"without depending on foreign aid after five or six years."},{"time":1163000,"text":"And for those of you who understand healthcare economics"},{"time":1165000,"text":"you know that all wealthy countries spend between nine and 11 percent of GDP"},{"time":1170000,"text":"on health care, except for the United States, we spend 16 --"},{"time":1172000,"text":"but that's a story for another day."},{"time":1175000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"We're now working with Partners in Health and the Ministry of Health in Rwanda"},{"time":1182000,"text":"and our Foundation folks to scale this system up."},{"time":1186000,"text":"We're also beginning to do this in Malawi and Lesotho."},{"time":1192000,"text":"And we have similar projects in Tanzania, Mozambique,"},{"time":1196000,"text":"Kenya and Ethiopia with other partners trying to achieve the same thing:"},{"time":1201000,"text":"to save as many lives as quickly as we can,"},{"time":1203000,"text":"but to do it in a systematic way that can be implemented nationwide"},{"time":1206000,"text":"and then with a model that can be implemented in any country in the world."},{"time":1210000,"text":"We need initial upfront investment to train doctors, nurses,"},{"time":1214000,"text":"health administration and community health workers throughout the country,"},{"time":1217000,"text":"to set up the information technology, the solar energy,"},{"time":1220000,"text":"the water and sanitation, the transportation infrastructure."},{"time":1223000,"text":"But over a five- to 10-year period,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"we will take down the need for outside assistance"},{"time":1228000,"text":"and eventually it will be phased out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1231000,"text":"My wish is that TED assist us in our work and help us to build"},{"time":1239000,"text":"a high-quality rural health system in a poor country, Rwanda,"},{"time":1243000,"text":"that can be a model for Africa,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"and indeed, for any poor country anywhere in the world."},{"time":1250000,"text":"My belief is that this will help us to build a more integrated world"},{"time":1256000,"text":"with more partners and fewer terrorists,"},{"time":1259000,"text":"with more productive citizens and fewer haters,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"a place we'd all want our kids and our grandchildren to grow up in."},{"time":1268000,"text":"It has been an honor for me, particularly, to work in Rwanda"},{"time":1274000,"text":"where we also have a major economic development project"},{"time":1277000,"text":"in partnership with Sir Tom Hunter, the Scottish philanthropist,"},{"time":1282000,"text":"where last year we, using the same thing with AIDS drugs,"},{"time":1285000,"text":"cut the cost of fertilizer and the interest rates on microcredit loans by 30 percent"},{"time":1291000,"text":"and achieved three- to four-hundred percent increases"},{"time":1295000,"text":"in crop yields with the farmers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1297000,"text":"These people have been through a lot and none of us, most of all me,"},{"time":1303000,"text":"helped them when they were on the verge of destroying each other."},{"time":1307000,"text":"We're undoing that now, and they are so over it and so into their future."},{"time":1313000,"text":"We're doing this in an environmentally responsible way."},{"time":1317000,"text":"I'm doing my best to convince them not to run the electric grid"},{"time":1321000,"text":"to the 35 percent of the people that have no access,"},{"time":1324000,"text":"but to do it with clean energy. To have responsible reforestation projects,"},{"time":1329000,"text":"the Rwandans, interestingly enough, have been quite good, Mr. Wilson,"},{"time":1333000,"text":"in preserving their topsoil."},{"time":1335000,"text":"There's a couple of guys from southern farming families --"},{"time":1339000,"text":"the first thing I did when I went out to this place"},{"time":1341000,"text":"was to get down on my hands and knees and dig in the dirt"},{"time":1343000,"text":"and see what they'd done with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1345000,"text":"We have a chance here to prove that a country"},{"time":1349000,"text":"that almost slaughtered itself out of existence"},{"time":1355000,"text":"can practice reconciliation, reorganize itself, focus on tomorrow"},{"time":1362000,"text":"and provide comprehensive, quality health care with minimal outside help."},{"time":1369000,"text":"I am grateful for this prize, and I will use it to that end."},{"time":1375000,"text":"We could use some more help to do this,"},{"time":1379000,"text":"but think of what it would mean if we could have a world-class health system"},{"time":1383000,"text":"in Rwanda -- in a country with a less-than-one-dollar-a-day-per-capita income,"},{"time":1388000,"text":"one that could save hundreds of millions of lives"},{"time":1392000,"text":"over the next decade if applied to every similarly situated country on Earth."},{"time":1399000,"text":"It's worth a try and I believe it would succeed."},{"time":1403000,"text":"Thank you and God bless you."},{"time":1406000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}